# Routes apt-get traffic from the infinito runner through the
# package-cache (Sonatype Nexus 3 OSS) pull-through proxy. Two repo
# entries to cover both Debian (`apt-debian`) and Ubuntu (`apt-ubuntu`)
# upstreams; the runner reads only the entry that matches its distro
# at runtime via apt's standard suite-resolution. The bootstrap helper
# pins debian -> bookworm and ubuntu -> jammy; older runners still
# resolve fine because Nexus serves the entire upstream tree.
#
# Uses the real mirror hostnames (mapped to the cache frontend via
# extra_hosts in compose/cache.override.yml), not the `package-cache`
# service name which coredns — the container's resolver — cannot resolve.
deb [trusted=yes] http://deb.debian.org/debian bookworm main
deb [trusted=yes] http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu jammy main
